      'Rare Fish Legal to Own in the US: 2026 Guide',
    metaDescription:
      'Which rare and exotic fish can you legally keep in the US? CITES rules, state restrictions, Lacey Act, and legal sourcing explained for collectors.',
    quickAnswerQuestion: 'What rare fish are legal to own in the US?',
    quickAnswer:
      'Most rare aquarium fish are legal to own in the US when captive-bred and properly documented. CITES-listed species like Asian Arowana require certificates and microchips. Freshwater stingrays are banned in roughly a dozen states. Piranhas are illegal in about 25 states. Snakehead fish are federally banned from live import. The Lacey Act prohibits trade in fish taken illegally from their home country. Always verify federal and state regulations before purchasing.',
