      'Arowanas (Osteoglossidae) and Snakeheads (Channidae) are both large, aggressive predatory fish popular with monster fish keepers, but they differ fundamentally. Arowanas are surface-dwelling predators that grow 60–120 cm, require 250+ gallon tanks, and include species valued at $400,000+ (Platinum Arowana). Snakeheads are ambush predators that grow 25–120 cm depending on species, can breathe atmospheric air, and are banned in many US states due to their invasive potential. Arowanas are legal in most jurisdictions (except Asian Arowana in the US); many Snakehead species are federally illegal in the USA.',
