      'Both Koi and Asian Arowanas rank among the most expensive ornamental fish in the world, but the price ceilings differ. The most expensive Koi ever sold was a Kohaku named "S Legend" that fetched $1.8 million at auction in 2018. The most expensive Arowana category is the Platinum Arowana (albino Scleropages formosus), with verified sales exceeding $400,000. Koi require outdoor ponds (1,000+ gallons) and live 25–35+ years. Arowanas require large indoor aquariums (250+ gallons) and live 15–20+ years. Both represent the pinnacle of fishkeeping prestige in their respective cultures.',
